|  | For the Years | Ended December 31, | 
--- | --- | --- | --- | ---
 | 2019 | 2018 | Increase/ (decrease) | % Change
Net revenues by platform: |  |  |  | 
Console | $1,920 | $2,538 | $(618) | (24)%
PC | 1,718 | 2,180 | (462) | (21)
Mobile and ancillary (1) | 2,203 | 2,175 | 28 | 1
Other (2) | 648 | 607 | 41 | 7
Total consolidated net revenues | $6,489 | $7,500 | $(1,011) | (13)

paragraph 1: Net Revenues by Platform
paragraph 2: The following tables detail our net revenues by platform (amounts in millions):
paragraph 3: (1) Net revenues from “Mobile and ancillary” include revenues from mobile devices, as well as non-platform-specific game-related revenues, such as standalone sales of toys and accessories.
paragraph 4: (2) Net revenues from “Other” primarily includes revenues from our Distribution business and the Overwatch League.
paragraph 5: Console
paragraph 6: The decrease in net revenues from console for 2019, as compared to 2018, was primarily due to:
paragraph 7: lower revenues recognized from the Destiny franchise (reflecting our sale of the publishing rights for Destiny to Bungie in December 2018); and lower revenues recognized from Call of Duty franchise catalog titles.
paragraph 8: The decrease was partially offset by revenues recognized from Crash Team Racing Nitro-Fueled, which was released in June 2019.
paragraph 9: PC
paragraph 10: The decrease in net revenues from PC for 2019, as compared to 2018, was primarily due to:
paragraph 11: lower revenues recognized from the Destiny franchise; and lower revenues recognized from Hearthstone.
paragraph 12: Mobile and Ancillary
paragraph 13: The increase in net revenues from mobile and ancillary for 2019, as compared to 2018, was primarily due to revenues recognized from Call of Duty: Mobile, which was released in October 2019.

qa.question: What does Net revenues from “Mobile and ancillary” include?
qa.answer: ['revenues from mobile devices, as well as non-platform-specific game-related revenues, such as standalone sales of toys and accessories.']
